modules.description: This module implements a binary search tree structure for spatial partitioning of points in a metric space, enabling efficient nearest neighbor queries, range searches, and tree traversal operations. It supports hierarchical data simplification through weighted averaging and string serialization, targeting applications in spatial data analysis and reduction of high-dimensional datasets. Core operations include tree construction with customizable heuristics, membership testing, and low-level modification of point-based hierarchies.

Implements a binary search tree for spatial partitioning of points in a metric space, supporting efficient nearest neighbor queries, range searches, and hierarchical data simplification via weighted averaging. Provides tree construction with customizable heuristics, membership testing, and serialization of tree paths to strings. Designed for spatial data analysis and reduction of high-dimensional datasets.
